Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
`name[: type]`. Type annotations (PEP 484) are optional but emitted when
present, formatted as a recursive HIR node so complex types (`List[int]`,
`Optional[Foo]`) work via the expression emitters.
@End Reasoning
@Implementation:
Emit name string; if "type" field present, emit ": " + recurse it.
@End Implementation
Process called "generate_parameter" takes context as Integer, hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Generate parameter

    Let emitter be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with context, 0

    Let name be proc get_dict_string_value from Dict with hir, "name"
    If name is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, name
    End If

    Let param_type be proc get_dict_hir_value from Dict with hir, "type"

    If param_type is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, ": "
        proc generate_node with context, param_type
    End If

    Return 1
End Process
